<subSubSection id="F2E78CC1A523FFF8FF52FB9EE124FAFE" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BA42DF4AA523FFF8FF52FB9EE124FAFE" blockId="18.[151,1436,1030,1595]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="88890358A523FFF8FF52FB9EE352FBFA" bold="true" box="[151,273,1030,1055]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Identical to 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FE58FB9EE018FBFA" box="[413,603,1030,1055]" class="Anthozoa" family="Microzoanthidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Microzoanthidae</taxonomicName>
(diagnosis of 
<bibRefCitation id="DE6CA2BBA523FFF8FD3FFB9EE1ABFBFA" author="Fujii" box="[762,1000,1030,1055]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" refString="Fujii, T. &amp; Reimer, J. D. (2011) Phylogeny of the highly divergent zoanthid family Microzoanthidae (Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) from the Pacific. Zoologica Scripta, 40, 418 - 443. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2011.00479. x" type="journal article" year="2011">
Fujii &amp; Reimer 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FC69FB9FE1ABFBFA" box="[940,1000,1031,1055]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Colonial 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FBA4FB9EE75DFBFA" box="[1121,1310,1030,1055]" class="Anthozoa" family="Microzoanthidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Microzoanthidae</taxonomicName>
free-living and lacking a scleroprotein skeleton. Known from temperate and tropical cryptic habitats in the Pacific Ocean at 
<quantity id="7D0572AFA523FFF8FF52FBD7E2ADFB83" box="[151,238,1103,1127]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" unit="m" value="11.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="0.0">
0â€“ 
<specimenCount id="ACFB14C3A523FFF8FF71FBD7E2ADFB83" box="[180,238,1103,1127]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" type="generic">23 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. Azooxanthellate. Polyps transparent or faintly red, expand to 
<quantity id="7D0572AFA523FFF8FC61FBD7E1A7FB83" box="[932,996,1103,1127]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
wide and 
<quantity id="7D0572AFA523FFF8FB93FBD7E6E7FB83" box="[1110,1188,1103,1127]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long. Capitular ridges largely imperceptible because of heavy encrustations. Oral disk calathiform and edged in a distinct zig-zag pattern (diagnosis expanded using data from 
<bibRefCitation id="DE6CA2BBA523FFF8FD8DFB0EE17CFB4A" author="Fujii" box="[584,831,1174,1199]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" refString="Fujii, T. &amp; Reimer, J. D. (2011) Phylogeny of the highly divergent zoanthid family Microzoanthidae (Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) from the Pacific. Zoologica Scripta, 40, 418 - 443. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2011.00479. x" type="journal article" year="2011">
Fujii &amp; Reimer 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FCC6FB0FE17CFB4A" box="[771,831,1175,1199]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Marginal musculature endodermal, 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FB29FB0EE70DFB4A" box="[1260,1358,1174,1199]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="299.5" valueMax="331.0" valueMin="268.0">268â€“331</number>
Îœm in length, composed of 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FE55FB22E395FB36" box="[400,470,1210,1235]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="13.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="10.0">10â€“16</number>
attachment points. Encrustations of column through ectoderm but not penetrating ectodermal surface of the mesoglea; elliptical lacunae just beneath ectodermal surface of mesoglea form an encircling sinus (diagnosis expanded using data presented here).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F2E78CC1A523FFF8FF02FABEE378F9DE" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BA42DF4AA523FFF8FF02FABEE378F9DE" blockId="18.[151,1436,1030,1595]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="88890358A523FFF8FF02FABEE378FADA" bold="true" box="[199,315,1318,1343]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Remarks.</emphasis>
The phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FD61FABEE108FADA" box="[676,843,1318,1343]" class="Anthozoa" family="Microzoanthidae" genus="Microzoanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="88890358A523FFF8FD61FABEE108FADA" box="[676,843,1318,1343]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Microzoanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as inferred by mitochondrial cytochrome oxidase (
<collectionCode id="DCEC478FA523FFF8FF5AFAD3E291FA86" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" box="[159,210,1355,1379]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">COI</collectionCode>
) and 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FED1FAD2E372FA86" box="[276,305,1354,1379]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="16.0">16</number>
s ribosomal (mt 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FE28FAD2E049FA86" box="[493,522,1354,1379]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="16.0">16</number>
S rDNA) genes (see 
<bibRefCitation id="DE6CA2BBA523FFF8FD3CFAD2E1A8FA86" author="Fujii" box="[761,1003,1354,1379]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" refString="Fujii, T. &amp; Reimer, J. D. (2011) Phylogeny of the highly divergent zoanthid family Microzoanthidae (Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) from the Pacific. Zoologica Scripta, 40, 418 - 443. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2011.00479. x" type="journal article" year="2011">
Fujii &amp; Reimer 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FC74FAD3E1A8FA86" box="[945,1003,1355,1379]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Figs 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FBF7FAD3E603FA87" box="[1074,1088,1355,1378]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="7.0">7</number>
&amp; S 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FBBFFAD3E6C6FA86" box="[1146,1157,1355,1379]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="1.0">1</number>
), is near the base of the 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FF52FAF6E356FA62" box="[151,277,1390,1415]" class="Anthozoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="order">Zoanthidea</taxonomicName>
and as the sister clade to 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FDF7FAF6E0FBFA62" box="[562,696,1390,1415]" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Isozoanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="88890358A523FFF8FDF7FAF6E0FBFA62" box="[562,696,1390,1415]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Isozoanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the 
<collectionCode id="DCEC478FA523FFF8FCCBFAF7E17DFA62" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" box="[782,830,1391,1415]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">COI</collectionCode>
tree) or all 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FC05FAF6E67DFA62" box="[960,1086,1390,1415]" class="Anthozoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="order">Zoanthidea</taxonomicName>
except 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FB50FAF6E758FA62" box="[1173,1307,1390,1415]" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Isozoanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="88890358A523FFF8FB50FAF6E758FA62" box="[1173,1307,1390,1415]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Isozoanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FAB5FAF6E7CEFA62" box="[1392,1421,1390,1415]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="16.0">16</number>
S tree). Although these phylogenies are incongruent (with each other and other published hypotheses, 
<emphasis id="88890358A523FFF8FAC0FA0BE76DFA4F" box="[1285,1326,1427,1450]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">e.g.</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="DE6CA2BBA523FFF8FAF8FA0AE357FA2A" author="Sinniger" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" refString="Sinniger, F., Montoya-Burgos, J. I., Chevaldonn, P. &amp; Pawlowski, J. (2005) Phylogeny of the order Zoantharia (Anthozoa, Hexacorallia) based on the mitochondrial ribosome genes. Marine Biology, 147, 1121 - 1128. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00227 - 005 - 0016 - 3" type="journal article" year="2005">
Sinniger 
<emphasis id="88890358A523FFF8FF52FA2FE292FA2A" box="[151,209,1462,1487]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FF1CFA2EE357FA2A" box="[217,276,1462,1487]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="DE6CA2BBA523FFF8FEE4FA2EE3EAFA2A" author="Swain" box="[289,425,1462,1487]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" refString="Swain, T. D. (2010) Evolutionary transitions in symbioses: dramatic reductions in bathymetric and geographic ranges of Zoanthidea coincide with loss of symbioses with invertebrates. Molecular Ecology, 19, 2587 - 2598. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 294 x. 2010.04672. x" type="journal article" year="2010">
Swain 
<number id="0C35CD6DA523FFF8FEAAFA2FE3EAFA2A" box="[367,425,1463,1487]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and poorly supported (both problems may be resolved by multigene analysis applied to comprehensive taxon sampling), they suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FD15FA42E134FA16" box="[720,887,1498,1523]" class="Anthozoa" family="Microzoanthidae" genus="Microzoanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="88890358A523FFF8FD15FA42E134FA16" box="[720,887,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Microzoanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may occupy a critical position near the origin of 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FF52FA66E356F9F2" box="[151,277,1534,1559]" class="Anthozoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="order">Zoanthidea</taxonomicName>
and could provide insight into the evolution of 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FCE0FA66E1E8F9F2" box="[805,939,1534,1559]" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Isozoanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="88890358A523FFF8FCE0FA66E1E8F9F2" box="[805,939,1534,1559]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Isozoanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and clarify relationships between the genera of 
<taxonomicName id="7DFDA4C9A523FFF8FF70F9BAE374F9DE" box="[181,311,1570,1595]" class="Anthozoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="order">Zoanthidea</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
